🕒 Weekday Schedule (Mon–Fri)
Time	Activity	Notes
7:00 AM – 8:00 AM	Light Learning	Read articles, watch short tutorials
8:00 AM – 8:30 AM	Planning	Review goals, update task list
2:00 PM – 10:00 PM	Main Study Block	As per daywise MERN + Cloud plan
10:00 PM – 10:30 PM	Wrap-up	Journal progress, plan next day
🧠 Weekend Study Plan (Sat–Sun)
Time	Activity	Focus
7:00 AM – 8:00 AM	Review	Recap weekly learnings
10:00 AM – 1:00 PM	Mini Project	Apply React/Node/AWS/Azure concepts
2:00 PM – 4:00 PM	Cloud Labs	IAM, EC2, App Service, Key Vault
5:00 PM – 7:00 PM	Security Practice	WAF, HTTPS, Secrets Manager, audits
8:00 PM – 9:00 PM	Documentation	Update GitHub, README, notes
✅ Time Management Tools (with use cases)
🗂️ Planning & Tracking
Notion: Create a daily planner, link resources, track progress.
Trello: Organize tasks by week/topic (React, Node, AWS, etc.).
Google Calendar: Block study hours, set reminders.
⏱️ Focus & Productivity
Pomofocus: Use Pomodoro technique (25 min focus + 5 min break).
Forest App: Stay off your phone while studying.
Todoist: Prioritize tasks and set recurring goals.
📊 Progress Monitoring
Clockify: Track time spent on each topic.
Obsidian: Take structured notes and link concepts.
GitHub Projects: Track issues, commits, and milestones.
